#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:564
msgid ""
"A friend of mine explored the island on his own and he told me of a big "
"lake\n"
"at the top of the mountain. I suggest we build the ships in this lake and "
"wait\n"
"until the island drowns beneath us. Then we can sail away. It is a bold "
"plan,\n"
"but I think, it could work."
msgstr ""
"Jedan moj prijatelj je samostalno  istražiao otok i pričao mi je o\n"
"velikom jezeru na samom vrhu planine. Predlažem da napravimo\n"
"brodić na ovom jezeru i čekamo dok se cijeli otok ne potopi ispod\n"
"nas. Tada možemo otploviti. Znam da nije neki plan, ali moga bi\n"
"funkcionirati."

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:343
msgid "A man comes to Jundlina"
msgstr "Čovjek prilazi Jundlini"

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:538
msgid "A young man approaches"
msgstr "Prilazi mladić"

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/elemental:11
msgid ""
"After landing on a mysterious island close to Atlantis, the remaining "
"Atlanteans struggle to make a new home for themselves."
msgstr ""
"Nakon iskrcavanja na ovaj zagonetni otok blizu Atlantide, preostali "
"atlantiđani se muče kako bi za sebe napravili novi dom."

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:308
msgid ""
"Ahh, but I think this is impossible to change. The preparing and eating of\n"
"food is something deeply ingrained in us Atlanteans - it is just a ceremony\n"
"that we need for our well being. So I guess we cannot take this away from\n"
"the individuals completely. But we might find a compromise in between: For "
"me,\n"
"making bread is a troublesome task: grinding the blackroot and corn to "
"flour\n"
"and then baking the bread is tedious and boring: I feel a more industrial\n"
"approach would be helpful here. I for one would love to just have fresh "
"bread\n"
"delivered to my house every day. Oooh and even more important: the smoking "
"of\n"
"fish and meat to cleanse them and improve their taste is terrible.  My house "
"is\n"
"full of smoke and stinks for weeks after it. Don't you think that this could "
"be\n"
"done in a special building were the side effects do not matter?  I think "
"those\n"
"two things would be accepted by the people and would reduce the cooking "
"times\n"
"without taking away the ritual."
msgstr ""
"Ahh, ali ja mislim da je ovo nemoguće promijeniti. Spremanje hrane i objedi\n"
"su nešto što je duboko usađeno u nama atlantiđanima. To je samo svečanost\n"
"koja nam je potrebna za opće dobro. Stoga mislim da to ne možemo oduzeti\n"
"sasvvim od pojedinaca. Ali možemo naći dogovor negdje na pola puta. Za\n"
"mene je pečenje kruha problematično: mljevenje crnog korijena i kukuruza\n"
"u brašno a zatim pečenje kruha je mučno i dosadno: Mislim da bi ovdje jako\n"
"pomogla industrijalizacija. Kao prvo ja bih volio kad bih samo dobio svježe\n"
"pečeni kruh dostavljen na moju adresu svaki dan. Oooh i što je još važnije:\n"
"dimljenje ribe i mesa te njihovo guljenje zbog boljeg okusa je strašno. "
"Moja\n"
"kuća je puna dima i mirisa  tjednima poslje. Zar ne misliš da bi ovo bilo "
"bolje\n"
"raditi u posebnim građevinama gdje posljedice ne bi nikome smetale? Mislim\n"
"da bi ove dvije stvari bile prihvaćene od ljudi i da bi smanjile vrijeme "
"pripreme\n"
"jela bez da moramo ukidati ritual."

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:512
msgid ""
"And yet another of these buildings. We know now that the tribe that built\n"
"them once had complete control over the island. But I am no longer so scared "
"of\n"
"potential enemies. We know so much of this island already and there is no "
"trace\n"
"of this old economy to be found. I am starting to relax, but I will not let\n"
"our guard down as we continue to explore this beautiful island. But without\n"
"obvious dangers I am feeling very much at home here already."
msgstr ""
"Još jedna u nizu ovih građevina. Sada nam je poznato da je pleme koje ih je\n"
"izgradilo imalo potpunu kontrolu nad otokom. Ali više nisam toliko uplašen\n"
"od mogućih neprijatelja. Jako dobro poznajemo ovaj otok i nema nikakvih\n"
"tragova ove stare civilizacije. Mogu se opustiti, ali neću raspustiti "
"stražu.\n"
"Štoviše, nastavljamo s istraživanjima ovog prekrasnog otoka. A bez\n"
"očiglednih opasnosti već se sada ovdje osjećam kao kod kuće."

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:495
msgid "Another building."
msgstr "Još jedna građevina."

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:121
msgid ""
"As all other tribes, the Atlanteans are also able to train soldiers: the\n"
"dungeon trains attack - the major attribute of the Atlanteans - and the\n"
"labyrinth trains evasion, health points and defense. The items produced by "
"the\n"
"industry are used to train better soldiers in the two training "
"buildings.<br><br>\n"
"- Build a dungeon and a labyrinth.<br>"
msgstr ""
"Kao i sva druga plemena, Atlantiđani su također sposobni trenirati\n"
"vojsku: tamnica pospješuje napad, koja je jedna od najboljih karakteristika\n"
"Atlantiđana, a labirint trenira izbjegavanje, zdravlje i obranu. Stvari \n"
"proizvedene u tvornicama se koriste u treniranju kako bi dobili bolje\n"
"vojnike. One su proizvode u građevinama za trening.<br><br>\n"
"- Izgradi tamnicu i labirint.<br>"

#: ../../campaigns/atl01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:132
msgid ""
"As your road network gets longer and more complicated, you should employ\n"
"horses to help out your carriers. Horses are bred in horsefarms using water "
"and\n"
"corn. A warehouse will also help to ensure your transportation system does "
"not\n"
"collapse."
msgstr ""
"Dok tvoja mreža puteva postaje veća i zahtjevnija, trebao bi koristiti "
"konje,\n"
"koji bi pomagali kod prenašanja stvari. Konji se uzgajajuu konjušnicama,\n"
"koristeći vodu i kukuruz. Skladište će također pomoći kako se tvoj sustav\n"
"opskrbe ne bi raspao."

